news.title: Maharashtra government allocates Rs 145 crore for infra development in rural Nashik
news.para: “State govt has earmarked Rs 145 crore under special additional outlay for urban pockets in the district that includes all 15 councils and nagar panchayats. This will help these urban areas to carry out developmental works,” said Nashik DPO Kiran Joshi.

news.title: Liquidator’s now required to convene SCC meetings at interval of 30 days: IBBI
news.para: Among the key amendments, the liquidator can reduce the reserve price by up to 25 per cent for assets with existing valuation of the Corporate Insolvency Resolution Process (CIRP) once during the liquidation process, provided it is approved by SCC.

news.title: Ensure financial service providers have regulatory nod for voluntary liquidation: IBBI to liquidators
news.para: FSPs notified by the central government after consulting financial regulators are allowed to undergo a voluntary liquidation process after obtaining prior permission of the appropriate regulator.

news.title: Australia's Dexus records statutory net loss of A$597.2 million in July-December 2023
news.para: CEO Darren Steinberg said he believed the office sector was nearing the bottom, which should in turn help unfreeze a market that has seen very few sales as buyers wait to see how far prices will fall.

news.title: Shriram Properties' net profit dips 17.35% in Q3 FY24
news.para: Shriram Properties' net consolidated total income stood at Rs 240.57 crore in Q3 FY24, a growth of 8.36 per cent from Rs 222.01 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Seven years on, Nagpur smart city yet to finish works
news.para: Now, with just four months left for the Smart Cities Mission deadline, it seems a herculean task for the NSSCDCL to finish the pending works in time. The flagship mission involves development of 100 cities into smart cities.

news.title: At least 60,000 houses to get underground drainage link in Madurai
news.para: Corporation officials told TOI that construction work will be completed in 36 months. The trial run of the system would be done for six months and maintenance will be carried out for the next 18 months by the contractor.

news.title: Allotted houses to stay out of liquidation: IBBI
news.para: According to one of the amendments by IBBI, wherever the corporate debtor has given possession to an allottee in a real estate project, such asset shall not form a part of the liquidation estate of the corporate debtor.

news.title: Ahmedabad metro phase-II trials to be done by March 2024
news.para: Metro officials said the entire stretch up to Mahatma Mandir will likely be completed by the end of the year.

news.title: Bengaluru: BBMP may increase property tax target by one-third for next year
news.para: The Palike plans to mop up Rs 6,000 crore in the coming year and is confident of achieving it by widening the tax net and plugging leaks.

news.title: Builders with over 50 housing units to get doorstep MahaRERA registration
news.para: Speaking at the concluding ceremony of the Credai-organised ‘Dalan 2024’ exhibition in Kolhapur on Wednesday, Devara said state govt aims to increase annual revenue generation through stamp duty registrations.

news.title: Godrej Properties acquires about 12.5-acre land parcel in Hyderabad
news.para: The development on this land is estimated to have a potential of approximately 4 million sq ft of saleable area comprising primarily of residential apartments with an estimated revenue potential of about Rs 3,500 crore.

news.title: Ghaziabad development body set to give nod to Wave City if builder mortgages Rs 400 crore property
news.para: Wave Group will, however, have to mortgage land and other property worth around Rs 400 crore with the GDA for the DPR to be approved.

news.title: Oyo Hotels & Homes may back out of IPO plan, opt for private raise
news.para: In a response to emailed queries by ET, Oyo said the information is inaccurate. Oyo’s first public offer filing was returned by the markets regulator in January 2023, requiring the SoftBank-backed firm to refile its draft red herring prospectus (DRHP) with updates and revisions.

news.title: Phoenix Mills records 69% rise in net profit at Rs 297 crore in Q3 FY24
news.para: Retail collections rose 30% to Rs 700 crore, while rental income from retail grew 33% to Rs 447 crore. Operating profit in retail business increased 27% to over Rs 435 crore. The company’s malls are operating at life-time high leased occupancy and trading levels.

news.title: Radius Group's MD denied bail in money laundering case
news.para: ​​​​​​​​The ED has accused Chhabria of playing a crucial role in diverting funds procured illegally by Yes Bank's founder Rana Kapoor and Dewan Housing Finance Limited (DHFL) promoter Kapil Wadhawan.

news.title: NCLT dismisses lawsuit demanding probe into affairs of Indiabulls Housing
news.para: Supertech Realtors alleged that Indiabulls Housing Finance had illegally deducted excess sums of money from its loan account.  In its lawsuit, the real estate firm alleged that the total sum accrued to it was ₹5,873 crore but Indiabulls Housing Finance deducted ₹6,150 crore from its loan account.

news.title: James Hardie’s net profit rise 39% to 179.9 million in Q3 FY24
news.para: The Dublin-based firm's adjusted net income for the three months ended Dec. 31 was $179.9 million, compared with $129.2 million last year.

news.title: Thiruvananthapuram: HC verdict on Dragonstone Realty's project likely in two weeks
news.para: Sources said the hearing proceedings related to the petition have been completed. The court’s judgment is crucial for the project, as it will have an impact on its future expansion in its non-SEZ component.

news.title: ITAT quashes income addition of Rs 40 lakh in hands of non-resident, holds agreement-value of flat as valid
news.para: The tax tribunal held that a sum of Rs 40.45 lakh which was the difference between the stamp duty value on the date of registration of the flat and the agreement value cannot be taxed in the hands of Shyamkumar Madhavdas Chugh hands as ‘Income from other sources’.
